aims-os-core (2.0+1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Heritage additions from AIMS Desktop 2020: bc (CLI calculator),
    lshw (hardware listing), smartmontools (disk SMART), zram-tools
    (compressed swap on RAM — big win on 4 GB lab laptops),
    wireless-tools (legacy iwconfig/iwlist still referenced in
    networking tutorials), rfkill (CLI wireless toggle),
    command-not-found.
  * Switch pkg-config to pkgconf — in Trixie pkg-config is a
    transitional package wrapping pkgconf; depending on pkgconf
    directly silences lintian and survives the transitional removal.

 -- AIMS Senegal IT <hakim@aims-senegal.org>  Fri, 22 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

aims-os-core (2.0) trixie; urgency=medium

  * v2.0 — rebase to Debian 13 Trixie.
    + No changes to the dependency list itself; everything we already
      pull (UFW, AppArmor, unattended-upgrades, fail2ban, firmware
      blobs, locales, ACPI/time-sync, fs/block tooling, build-essential,
      gfortran) is present in Trixie with the expected names.

 -- AIMS Senegal IT <hakim@aims-senegal.org>  Thu, 21 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

aims-os-core (1.0) bookworm; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
    + Pulls the AIMS OS system-level baseline: UFW + AppArmor +
      unattended-upgrades + fail2ban security tooling, firmware
      blobs for typical lab hardware, French locale and desktop,
      ACPI / time-sync daemons, filesystem and block-layer tooling,
      everyday CLI utilities, build-essential + gfortran toolchain.

